bankruptcy /ˈbæŋkrʌptsɪ/

(bankruptcies) 

1. N-UNCOUNT Bankruptcy is the state of being bankrupt. 破产 (状态) [商业] 

例： Pan Am is the second airline in two months to file for bankruptcy. 泛美航空公司是两个月内第二家申请破产的航空公司。 

2. N-COUNT A bankruptcy is an instance of an organization or person going bankrupt. 破产 (事件) [商业] 

例： The number of corporate bankruptcies climbed in August. 企业破产的数量在8月份增加了。

